						               													<description>Champions Challenge&amp;#10;&amp;#10;INTRO:&amp;#10;The time has come once again. A chance for the divided clans of Rivaland to prove who is&amp;#10;mightiest. Each clan will send forth their greatest warrior to compete in the Champions Challenge.&amp;#10;The victor will be rewarded greatly as well as claim the title of the mightiest clan throughout&amp;#10;Rivaland. That is of course, if there is a victor at all. Known only to the King and his closest&amp;#10;trustees, the Challenge is actually a real threat against the kingdom. Thus meaning it will place the&amp;#10;Champions in real danger. They must face deadly monsters, tricky traps, and even the threat of&amp;#10;each other. However, they may be forced to work together if they wish to survive.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GAMEPLAY:&amp;#10;The game starts by choosing the Challenge. Each challenge is played on a different Location tile&amp;#10;and a deck of cards with unique monsters, traps, events, and Boss Monster. Next the players choose&amp;#10;their Champions. There are four clans to choose from with a male and female version of each.&amp;#10;The Champions have unique attributes which make playing each one a bit different. On a turn,&amp;#10;each player has 3 Action points to spend. Actions include recovering, exploring, attacking,&amp;#10;making skill checks, and commanding a pet! While exploring, they will earn Challenge points for&amp;#10;defeating monsters and escaping traps. Each Challenge has a few events that must occur before the&amp;#10;Boss shows up. This can happen at anytime during the game and players might not always be ready!&amp;#10;Players will find powerful treasures like weapons, shields, and talismans that will make them more&amp;#10;powerful. Collecting as many challenge points as possible before the Challenge is completed is the&amp;#10;primary goal, next to surviving of course!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Clans of Rivaland:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Slayers&amp;#10;Shaman&amp;#10;Marksman&amp;#10;Machinist&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
